-- 888’s Mattingley ‘Pleased’ With Italy, ‘Cautious’ on U.S. Market
-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 2012-04-24T07:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/888-s-mattingley-pleased-with-italy-cautious-on-u-s-market.html
888 Holdings Plc (888)  Chief Executive
Officer Brian Mattingley said he is “very pleased” with the
company’s progress in  Italy  and remains “cautious” on the
opening of the U.S. market.  “We are very pleased with what we are seeing in Italy,”
Mattingley said in a phone interview today. “I’m very cautious
on the U.S. market. It will open, when it will open nobody is
sure. We want to concentrate more on territories where we know
they are opening.”  888 began trading in Italy in July 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colm Heatley in Belfast at 
